markdown.content:
## ![Cyware Logo](https://cdn.cyware.com/logos/cyware-intel-exchange.png) Cyware Intel Exchange - Cyware IOCs Overview
---
#### This dashboard shows IOCs from Cyware Intel Exchange as normalized into the Google SecOps Entity Context Graph (ECG).

dashboardQueries.query:

graph.metadata.product_name = "Cyware Intel Exchange"

$date=timestamp.get_timestamp(graph.metadata.interval.start_time.seconds, "%Y-%m-%d")
$entityid = graph.metadata.product_entity_id
$severity = graph.metadata.threat.severity
match:
    $date, $severity
outcome:
    $count=count_distinct($entityid)
order:
    $date asc
limit:
    10000

dashboardQueries.name: 34b4d1aa-8332-44ed-a601-f2d649df8646
dashboardQueries.query:
graph.metadata.vendor_name = "Cyware"
graph.metadata.product_name = "Cyware Intel Exchange"

$score = graph.metadata.threat.risk_score
$entityid = graph.metadata.product_entity_id

$risk_category = if(graph.metadata.threat.risk_score = 0, "None", if(graph.metadata.threat.risk_score >= 1 and graph.metadata.threat.risk_score <= 29, "Low", if(graph.metadata.threat.risk_score >= 30 and graph.metadata.threat.risk_score <= 69, "Medium", if(graph.metadata.threat.risk_score >= 70, "High", "Unknown"))))
match:
    $risk_category
outcome:
    $count = count_distinct($entityid)
order:
    $count desc
limit:
    15
